main event: A civilian observed a round flashing red light, similar in size to a baseball held at arm's length, flying in a straight course for three minutes in Waupun, Wisconsin on 14 May 1956.
interesting points: The object was observed for three minutes, displaying a flashing red light and flying on a straight course, indicating a probable aircraft-generated sighting.
The report considers the possibility of the object being a navigational light from an aircraft, balloon, or astronomical object.
The observation location was in Waupun, Wisconsin.
The source of the observation was a civilian.
The observation did not include any photographs.
